name: Chad Daybell
summary: In a shocking turn of events, Chad Daybell, a self-proclaimed doomsday author, has been found guilty of murdering his wife, Lori Vallow Daybell, as well as his girlfriend Tammy Daybell's two children, Joshua "JJ" Vallow and Tylee Ryan. The trial, dubbed the "zombie murder" case, concluded with Daybell facing the death penalty for his heinous crimes. The prosecution presented evidence suggesting that Daybell and Vallow shared a belief in a doomsday cult, leading them to plan and execute the murders of their loved ones in preparation for the end of the world. The jury unanimously found Daybell guilty on all charges, including first-degree murder, conspiracy to commit murder, and grand theft. The sentencing phase of the trial is underway, with the jury considering whether Daybell should receive the death penalty or life in prison without the possibility of parole.

However, he also expressed "high hopes" for the tournament, emphasizing that he is taking a relaxed approach and viewing it as a "free hit." Djokovic survived a grueling five-set epic against Lorenzo Musetti in his opening match, which ended after 3 AM, becoming the latest-ever finish in French Open history. Despite the challenging match, Djokovic remained composed and ultimately emerged victorious, showcasing his resilience and determination.
